Samsung Galaxy M30s AnTuTu, Geekbench, GFX, PCMark Score

  • Samsung Galaxy M30s AnTuTu benchmark score is 135,678.
  • Samsung Galaxy M30s Geekbench single-core score is 304 and multi-core benchmark score is 1,273
  • GFXBench Manhattan score for Samsung Galaxy M30s is 1,060.0 and GFXBench T-Rex score is 1,624.0
  • Samsung Galaxy M30s PCMark battery performance time is 14h 29m

Samsung Galaxy M30s Benchmark Scores Overview

Samsung Galaxy M30s is powered by the Samsung Exynos 9 Octa 9611. The processor is Octa core (2.3 GHz, Quad core, Cortex A73 + 1.7 GHz, Quad core, Cortex A53) that uses 64 bit architecture and Mali-G72 MP3 GPU. It runs on Android v9.0 (Pie) operating system with 4 GB RAM and 64 GB ROM.

Samsung Galaxy M30s AnTuTu Score:

Samsung Galaxy M30s has an overall AnTuTu score of 135,678. The benchmark app also gives individual scores for CPU, Memory, GPU, and UX tests. Samsung Galaxy M30s scored 52,575 for CPU, 9,726 for Memory, 40,343 for GPU, and 33,034 for UX test.
